snippet.textDisplay: To any dog owners out there looking for a safe way to transport dogs in cars: an appropriately sized car cage is a good option. The car needs to be big enough for the dog to be comfortable, but not so big they'll bounce around in there. The limited size of the cage works the same way our seatbelts do; they keep the dogs from flying through the air and being hurt on impact in the event of a sudden stop or (worst case) a crash. A good dog car cage retailer can help you find the right size cage for your breed. Of course the dog shouldn't be locked in the cage for longer periods of time and whenever you stop for a toilet/snack break on your drive, remember that your dog might want to stretch its legs and eat/drink/go to the bathroom as well.
